properties.Name: EEZ
properties.Description: South Korea (the Republic of Korea) has declared baselines around most of the peninsula. From these basepoints, we drew an exclusive economic zone (EEZ) and territorial sea to 200 and 12 nautical, cutting off the EEZ at the median line with South Korea’s neighbors. Along the western border with North Korea, we used the Northern Limit Line as the boundary. Unlike Japan, South Korea does not claim an EEZ from the Liancourt Rocks and we therefore ignored these islets in drawing the median line in that area.
